The paper deals with wireless networks and their performance in terms of achievable sum rates, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the impact of distributed decisions on network performance, which is related to networked systems (cs.NI) and control systems (cs.SY). The use of local message passing and protocol abstraction is also relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM) applications.
